  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>paultag found one bug in this, which is that when we experimentally modify the
filename to see we should use old-style filenames, we mutate state inside the
function, resulting in showing the old-style filename to the user in an error
message.

I added a patch on top to address that, and am now deploying this!</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2510">msg2510 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: paulproteus</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-09-20.20:14:49</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The attached patches clean up the recursive diff mission so that:

* It does "from x.y import *" less often

* The filenames no longer contain the string [aA]ubergine

* The checker accepts both the old filenames and the new filenames, in case
people had an extracted tarball with the old filenames.

Attaching the patch for now since gitorious isn't up.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2504">msg2504 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: paulproteus</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-09-20.15:16:52</th>
